<%#= cms_snippet_content('childrens-country-fair', @cms_site).html_safe %>
<div id='ccf-info' class='expanded row bottom-shadow content-box special-box'>
  <!--image-->
  <div class='small-12 columns'>
    <%= image_tag('hattie-ccf.jpg', class: 'bottom-shadow') %>
  </div>

  <!--header-->
  <div class='row expanded' data-equalizer data-equalize-on='large' id='header-eq'>
    <div class='small-12 large-6 columns left' data-equalizer-watch>

      <h1 class='hi-li padded green kaushan center'>
        The Children's Country Fair
      </h1>

    </div>
    <div class='small-12 large-6 columns right' data-equalizer-watch>
      <h2 class='green padded center content-box' style='margin-top:20px;'>
        <strong>Saturday, October 8, 2016 11am-3pm</strong>
      </h2>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr>
  
  <!--content-->
  <div id="ccf-welcome">
    <div class='small-11 small-centered columns'>
      <p class='p-box'>
        Please join us for a family and child-centered event that includes wagon and pony rides, artisans, country fair food, music, cake-walk, obstacle course, dunk tank, face-painting and dress-up, water play, bubble-making, penny toss, and much more! Check back often for details and activity shift sign-up coming soon!
      </p>
      <p class='p-box'>
        Don't forget to check out the <strong><em><a href='#fun-run'>Little Run on the Prairie!</a></em></strong>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr>

  <!--ACTIVITY EXAMPLES-->
  <div class='small-12 columns content-box padded p-box'>
    <div class='small-11 small-centered columns'>
      <ul id='activity-examples' class='padded'>
        <li>Help place tables, chairs, canopies, signs, materials, trash and composting bins.</li>
        <li>Organize items, label and price as needed, collect money and tickets for items purchased, prepare root beet floats.</li>
        <li>Assemble orders, prepare sandwiches, etc. , collect money and tickets for meals.</li>
        <li>Bring a creative spirit and have fun!  Supplies and sample design inspirations are provided.</li>
        <li>This activity will make you laugh and get you wet.</li>
        <em><span class="brighten hidden" data-redactor-tag="span">Ideal for parent and child team</span></em>

        <li>This activity is located at the sand box by the farmhouse and is a perennial favorite among the younger set.</li>
        <em><span class="brighten hidden" data-redactor-tag="span">Ideal for parent and child team</span></em>

        <li>You will start and stop the music and give the winner a cake!</li>
        <em><span class="brighten hidden" style="font-size: 1vw;" rel="font-size: 1vw;" data-redactor-tag="span">Ideal for parent and elementary child team</span></em>

        <li>Assist children as they assume new identities from Prairie Hill's expansive costume collection.</li>
        <em><span class="brighten hidden" data-redactor-tag="span">Ideal for parent and child team</span></em>

        <li>Supervise, cheer, and assist children as they navigate a fun challenge course for young children.</li>
        <li>Supplies (pennies and cups) will be on hand. Stock cups as needed.</li>
        <em><span class="brighten hidden" style="font-size: 1vw;" rel="font-size: 1vw;" data-redactor-tag="span">Ideal for parent and elementary child team</span></em>

        <li>Don a fun outfit with many pockets. Collect a ticket and invite the player to check a pocket.  Supplies (including outfit!) is provided.</li>
        <li>One person will take tickets, the other will get dunked! (you can swap spots). Bring a change of clothes.</li>
        <li>Collect cash ($2 per car; musicians and vendors park free) and direct cars to parking in the pasture. Dress for the weather. Bring a water bottle. We provide a chair, safety vest, and money aprons. Parkers will be stationed on highway 77 at the pasture entrance and in the pasture.</li>
        <li>Use your own camera and share the photos you take with the Fair Planning team to be distributed to the community.</li>
        <li>Someone ready to run from one end of the fair to the other as needed by various members of the fair committee.</li>
        <li>Take tickets. Volunteer will need some sense of how to throw a lasso.</li>
        <li>Collect tickets.</li>
        <em><span class="brighten hidden" data-redactor-tag="span">Ideal for parent to volunteer with their young child</span></em>.

        <li>Count tickets, collect money, encourage raffle and fund raising package sales.</li>
        <li>Ideal for an Older Elementary or Adolescent student. Assist participants in drawing simple animals.  Samples will be provided.</li>
        <li>Assist children (with someone from Dixon Power Systems) as they get their hands wet creating energy.</li>
        <li>Assist Children (with someone from Lux) in creating their own button and bookmark designs.</li>
        <li>Adult volunteer to run corn cobbing machine. Will need to stay alert to assist children with cranking while keeping hands out of the machine.</li>
        <li>Assist children with monor injuries. Call EMS if needed. First aid supplies are included.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!--FUN RUN-->
<div id='fun-run' class='expanded row bottom-shadow content-box special-box'>

  <h1 class='hi-li padded green kaushan center'>
    Little Run on the Prairie!
  </h1>

  <div class='small-6 columns left'>
    <%= image_tag('swanson.jpg', class: 'bottom-shadow') %>
    <div class='row'>
      <div class='small-8 small-centered columns'>
        <p class='p-box'>
          <a href='https://www.facebook.com/events/119411401842459/'>Facebook Event</a> |
          <a href='http://getmeregistered.com/LittleRunOnThePrairie'>Register Online</a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class='small-6 columns right'>
    <h3>Saturday, October 8th</h3>
    <h3>Packet Pick up 9:30 AM</h3>

    A 1-mile fun run for children, youth and adults!

    T-shirt with registration by September 16th

    same day registration at 10:00 in the pasture

    Parents are welcome to run with their children! Children need not run the entire length of the mile, they can run/ walk as much as they can! 

    Children's Country Fair immediately following the run 11-3pm. 
    <p>
      <em>Non-competitive fun run -- everyone is a winner :)</em>
    </p>
    <h3>Cost-$10</h3>
    <h3>ADDITIONAL DONATIONS WELCOME</h3>

        Many thanks to Scott Swanson, MD for the title sponsorship of this event.
  </div>
</div>
